# Core project rules

- Keep changes minimal and consistent with the current small-app structure (single-page Vite app under `src/`).
- Prefer **TypeScript-first** solutions and keep `strict` compiler settings happy (no unused locals/params).
- Avoid adding new dependencies unless absolutely necessary; prefer plain React + DOM APIs.
- Maintain accessibility basics: labels for inputs, sensible aria labels, keyboard support for interactive controls.
- Don’t introduce persistent side effects during render; keep effects scoped and cleaned up.
- When you change behavior, update UI copy (Arabic/English) consistently and keep strings user-friendly.
- Use the existing scripts for validation: `npm run build` (TypeScript + Vite build) should stay clean.

